    "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Acceptance Threshold",
    "requirementText": "The CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) for the candidate device shall not exceed 1.45 when compared against the predicate device hemolysis baseline across all evaluated flow-speed operating points. This threshold is derived from the allowable hemolysis margin for Class II CPB devices under standard cardiopulmonary bypass flow conditions.",
    "rationale": "An RH threshold of 1.45 provides the regulatory acceptance margin for relative hemolysis performance. Values below this threshold indicate the candidate device does not substantially increase hemolysis relative to the predicate and is therefore acceptable for CPB use."
